public interface Visitable<Type>

Applies a visitor to a subset of the objects in a container.

Convenience object to allow applying a Visitable.Visitor callback over some subset of the elements of a container.

Visitors can not mofify the value or object reference stored in the container.

The value returned by a visitor is used to signal early stops of the traversal, and is aggregated into a final result available to the application.

See Also:
Iterator, Iterable.iterator(), Operable

Nested Class Summary
static interface Visitable.Visitor<Type,Par>
          A callback, or procedure, used by the visit(net.varkhan.base.containers.Visitable.Visitor, Par).

A Visitor callback takes a single object of the type supported by the container, processes that element, and returns a long value that signifies the end of the iteration if negative, and is added to the total visiting count otherwise.
